About the company:

Avenue Code is the leading software consultancy focused on delivering end-to-end development solutions for digital transformation across every vertical. We’re privately held, profitable, and have been on a solid growth trajectory since day one. We care deeply about our clients, our partners, and our people. We prefer the word ‘partner’ over ‘vendor’, and our investment in professional relationships is a reflection of that philosophy. We pride ourselves on our technical acumen, our collaborative problem-solving ability, and the warm professionalism of our teams.

More than 3 years of working on diversity and inclusion strategies, Avenue Code still believes that recognizing the difference and promoting a safe place, job opportunities, representativeness, and support is the best way to make the social transformation happen. All job openings aim to promote employment and recognition of diversity pillars.

About the opportunity:

We’re looking for a Senior Java Engineer with experience in Kafka to join a project with a client that delivers world-class solutions across the top IT platforms and technologies. This person will be responsible for performing Global Delivery Services. The Technical Consultant is an experienced professional, with a full understanding of practice specialization. Employ suitable methods and techniques to ensure the optimum execution and delivery of the service as required.

Responsibilities:

Work closely with the Engagement Manager to provide Specialist Operational Support to the project and delivery of service;
Deliver and support defined architectural solutions and relevant technology in adherence to the agreed solution design;
Design, implement, and maintain applications, with considerations for high availability and optimized performance, whilst adhering the industry standards and best practices;
Participation in all stages of the development lifecycle process, including code development, testing/debugging, implementation, release preparation, and production.
Required Qualifications:

Solid experience in the software development lifecycle;
Hands-on experience with Java Development and Spring;
Experience with Data Streaming: Kafka;
Solid experience with Microservices and APIs;
Cloud knowledge: AWS, GCP, or Azure;
Exposure to ETL and Data Processing;
Stakeholder Management skills: Clearly and effectively communicates with customers and ensures that they understand and have visibility of activities and deliverables;
Experience working in an agile (scrum) environment;
Advanced English skills (this person will be working in a multicultural team).
Nice to Have:

Desirable experience in DevOps.

Bring your passion, talent and knowledge to the HyperSense team. We are a one-stop mobile and web software development company located in Bucharest, Romania. The apps we work on are diverse and challenging, a few examples retail, banking, media or enterprise apps, IoT projects, start-up projects, integrations with custom hardware and the list can go on.
We are looking for dynamic, reliable, and experienced Flutter Developers which can take part in our client's successful project.

Responsibilities

Work in a multi-disciplinary agile team delivering mobile and web applications in large-scale and global projects
Interact with our clients to understand their needs;
Transform the business requirements into feature specifications;
Participate in high level estimates for large work packages;
Analyse requirements, design solutions and develop software artefacts;
Ensuring high performance on mobile and web applications;
Coordinating the workflow between the graphic designer and yourself;
Research on various technologies useful for the project and keep in touch with the evolution of the industry;
Contribute to and promote good software engineering practices across the team.

